            <practice ID="ShroudingTheDeceasedAccordingToGender">
                <explanation>
                    <div>In Islam, it is best to shroud men in three pieces of cloth and women in five pieces of cloth. The minimum in which the deceased may be shrouded, which fulfills the obligatory duty, is a single piece of cloth that covers the entire body.</div>
                </explanation>
                <names>
                    <name language="English">Shrouding female deceased in five pieces of cloth</name>
                </names>
